        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "When using a schema-name in Zend_Db_Table, it always throws a Syntax-Error in Zend_Db_Adapter_Pdo_Sqlite. So there seems to be a bug in lines 180 to 184. The lines\n{code}        if ($schemaName) {\n            $sql = \"PRAGMA table_info($schemaName.$tableName)\";\n        } else {\n            $sql = \"PRAGMA table_info($tableName)\";\n        }{code}should be{code}        if ($schemaName) {\n            $sql = \"PRAGMA $schemaName.table_info($tableName)\";\n        } else {\n            $sql = \"PRAGMA table_info($tableName)\";\n        }{code}This works fine for me."
        },
